  "prompt": "What would be the top 10% bay area salary for PhD with 7 years experience, in different technical fields?",
  "response": "The top 10% salary for a PhD with 7 years of experience in the Bay Area varies significantly depending on the technical field. Below are approximate salary ranges for high-earning roles in different fields, based on 2023 data and industry trends:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Software Engineering / Artificial Intelligence (AI) / Machine Learning (ML)**\n   - **Salary Range:** $300,000 - $500,000+  \n     (Including base salary, bonuses, and stock options at top tech companies like Google, Meta, or OpenAI.)\n\n---\n\n### **2. Data Science / Analytics**\n   - **Salary Range:** $250,000 - $400,000  \n     (For senior roles at companies like LinkedIn, Salesforce, or Netflix.)\n\n---\n\n### **3. Biotechnology / Pharmaceuticals**\n   - **Salary Range:** $200,000 - $350,000  \n     (For roles in R&D, computational biology, or bioinformatics at companies like Genentech or Gilead Sciences.)\n\n---\n\n### **4. Hardware Engineering (Semiconductors, Robotics, etc.)**\n   - **Salary Range:** $250,000 - $400,000  \n     (For roles at companies like NVIDIA, Intel, or Tesla.)\n\n---\n\n### **5. Cybersecurity**\n   - **Salary Range:** $220,000 - $380,000  \n     (For senior roles at companies like Palo Alto Networks or CrowdStrike.)\n\n---\n\n### **6. Quantum Computing**\n   - **Salary Range:** $250,000 - $450,000  \n     (For niche roles at companies like IBM, Google Quantum, or startups in the field.)\n\n---\n\n### **7. Renewable Energy / Cleantech**\n   - **Salary Range:** $180,000 - $300,000  \n     (For roles in advanced research or engineering at companies like Tesla or Bloom Energy.)\n\n---\n\n### **8. Financial Technology (FinTech)**\n   - **Salary Range:** $250,000 - $450,000  \n     (For roles in quantitative analysis, blockchain, or AI-driven financial modeling at companies like Stripe or Robinhood.)\n\n---\n\n### **9. Aerospace / Space Technology**\n   - **Salary Range:** $200,000 - $350,000  \n     (For roles in advanced engineering or research at companies like SpaceX or NASA-affiliated contractors.)\n\n---\n\n### **10. Telecommunications / Networking**\n   - **Salary Range:** $220,000 - $380,000  \n     (For roles in advanced R&D or systems engineering at companies like Cisco or Verizon.)\n\n---\n\n### **Notes:**\n- **Total Compensation:** In the Bay Area, total compensation often includes base salary, annual bonuses, and stock options or equity, which can significantly increase earnings, especially at startups or tech giants.\n- **Industry Variability:** Salaries can vary widely depending on the company, the specific role, and individual negotiation skills.\n- **Startups vs. Established Companies:** Startups may offer lower base salaries but higher equity potential, while established companies typically offer more stable compensation packages.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, consult platforms like **Levels.fyi**, **Glassdoor**, or **Payscale**, or network with professionals in your specific field.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
